# init(parent:textList:contents:markerAttributes:children:)

**Initializer**

Creates a text list element with the parent, list elements, nesting level, and marker attributes you provide.

## Declaration

```swift
init(parent: NSTextListElement?, textList: NSTextList, contents: NSAttributedString?, markerAttributes: [NSAttributedString.Key : Any]? = nil, children: [NSTextListElement]?)
```

## Parameters

- **parent**: The parent `NSTextListElement` of this element, if any.
- **textList**: The [doc://com.apple.uikit/documentation/UIKit/NSTextList] to add elements to.
- **contents**: An [doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/Foundation/NSAttributedString] that contains the contents of the text list element.
- **markerAttributes**: A dictionary of [doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/Foundation/NSAttributedString/Key] keys and IDs that describe the marker attributes.
- **children**: An array of [doc://com.apple.uikit/documentation/UIKit/NSTextListElement] elements.

## Create a text list element

- **init(children:textList:nestingLevel:)**: Creates a text list element with the list elements and nesting level you provide.
- **init(contents:markerAttributes:textList:children:)**: Creates a text list element with the list elements, nesting level, and marker attributes you provide.
